{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775867348723,"sessionID":"ses_2860ed2feffeB7qcd2ac0NdJM2","part":{"id":"prt_d79f146ef001V1k7N1ZVjxupDG","messageID":"msg_d79f13cee00113UrUzlAqR0L4C","sessionID":"ses_2860ed2feffeB7qcd2ac0NdJM2","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867366628,"sessionID":"ses_2860ed2feffeB7qcd2ac0NdJM2","part":{"id":"prt_d79f14e2d001I5bk4HIZ1QrUhv","messageID":"msg_d79f13cee00113UrUzlAqR0L4C","sessionID":"ses_2860ed2feffeB7qcd2ac0NdJM2","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_563f630ae27944b191848052","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) providing `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` for creating code interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane).\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe Python SDK enables users to programmatically create and manage Code Interpreter sessions and invoke AgentRuntime workloads through the AgentCube infrastructure. It provides a high-level Python API abstracting the underlying HTTP communication with the control plane and data plane.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **Public API** (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n   - `CodeInterpreterClient` — session lifecycle, command execution, file operations\n   - `AgentRuntimeClient` — session bootstrapping, payload invocation\n\n2. **Control Plane** (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n   - `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` — POST to `/v1/code-interpreter`\n   - `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` — DELETE session with 404-as-success handling\n\n3. **Data Plane** (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n   - `execute_command()` — POST to `api/execute` with JSON command array\n   - `run_code()` — write timestamped `.py` file + execute via `execute_command`\n   - `write_file()` / `upload_file()` / `download_file()` / `list_files()` — file operations\n   - Session header management: `x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n4. **Data Plane** (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n   - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` — session bootstrap via GET, invoke via POST with JSON payload\n\n5. **Utilities**\n   - HTTP session factory with connection pooling\n   - Token file reader for Kubernetes service account\n   - Logger factory\n\n6. **Exception Hierarchy** (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n   - `AgentCubeError` (base), `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Non-Python language SDKs (Go, TypeScript, etc.)\n- Configuration dataclass (settings distributed across components)\n- Authentication beyond bearer token / service account file\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n| Stakeholder | Impact |\n|-------------|--------|\n| SDK consumers | New Python library; enables programmatic access to AgentCube |\n| Control plane | New client traffic patterns (session create/delete) |\n| Router (data plane) | New traffic for code execution and file operations |\n| Documentation | Need to document usage, environment variables, and error handling |\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n| Alternative | Rationale for Rejection |\n|-------------|------------------------|\n| Use existing `openai` Python library | Does not support AgentCube's custom session/header protocol |\n| Generate SDK from OpenAPI spec | Spec not available; hand-crafted for clarity |\n| Single `Configuration` class | Distributed defaults match existing deployment patterns |\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Use `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` for connection pooling\n- Timeout defaults: read=120s, connect=5.0s\n- Session header: lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- `CodeInterpreterClient` supports context manager for automatic cleanup\n- `AgentRuntimeClient` bootstraps session ID via GET header inspection\n\n## Timeline Estimate\n\n- Size: M (medium)\n- Phases: API design → implementation → unit tests → integration tests → release","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775867366618,"end":1775867366625}}}}
